race.comment: FAYOLA BABY (5) comes through a couple of handy trials in readiness for this. She has plenty of upside and was only 2.3L off the winner in Maiden company first-up last campaign. She looks well-placed at this level and appears to be the one to beat. RAINLINE (4) looks poised to strike third-up into the campaign following a 2.1L defeat most recently at Belmont as favourite. She now lands here with Faithfull in the saddle and the chance to sit a little closer than she has done in recent efforts. Can land the knockout blow. URQUHARTS BLUFF (2) drops back to this level today after holding his own on a Heavy deck at Belmont in a CL3. That form has worked out alright and getting back on top of the ground looks a positive for him. Can make his presence felt. MAVIS MYRTLE (8) is better than she showed last time out and can improve back in trip. WORK HOME FRONT (3) has claims of a good trial coming into this.
